message.content: The first ten positive multiples of $13$ are $13$, $2 \cdot 13$, $3 \cdot 13$, $\ldots$, $10 \cdot 13$. This is an arithmetic sequence with first term $13$, common difference $13$, and last term $10 \cdot 13 = 130$. Thus, the sum of this arithmetic sequence is equal to $$\frac{13 + 130}{2} \cdot 10 = \frac{143}{2} \cdot 10 = \boxed{715}.$$
